gnome_parse_locale() leaves country untouched for locales without a territory,
such as C.

Solaris exposes this via 03-enable-existing-user-mode.patch, which enables the
existing-user path through get_locale_infos(). That path can then pass stack
garbage in country to gnome_xkb_info_get_layouts_for_country(), crashing in
strlen().

Initialize lang and country to NULL before calling gnome_parse_locale().

--- a/gnome-initial-setup/pages/keyboard/cc-input-chooser.c
+++ b/gnome-initial-setup/pages/keyboard/cc-input-chooser.c
@@ -399,7 +399,7 @@ get_locale_infos (CcInputChooser *chooser)
         CcInputChooserPrivate *priv = cc_input_chooser_get_instance_private (chooser);
 	const gchar *type = NULL;
 	const gchar *id = NULL;
-	gchar *lang, *country;
+	gchar *lang = NULL, *country = NULL;
 	GList *list;
 
 	if (gnome_get_input_source_from_locale (priv->locale, &type, &id)) {
